In 2011, I received a MSc in bioinformatics from the University of Tübingen, Germany. Next, I moved to Denmark to do a PhD in the Molecular Oncology group in the Health Faculty of the University of Southern Denmark. There, I developed a complex software pipeline reaching from RNAi drug target discovery using robotic automation systems down to systems biology evaluation.
